   <taskbody>
      <prereq class="- topic/section task/prereq ">
         <ul class="- topic/ul ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">The role of the logged-in user should be <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Fund Manager</uicontrol>.</p>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </prereq>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">You can deactivate an active <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Global Fund List</uicontrol> record. If a fund source is marked as inactive, then the  fund source will not be available for projects.<note class="- topic/note ">Deactivating a global fund source that is already assigned to a project does not change the
assigned fund source data of the project.</note>
         </p>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the module menu, click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Home</uicontrol>. </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Enterprise Dashboard</uicontrol> is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the navigation pane, expand the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Fund Management </uicontrol> folder, and then click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Global Fund List</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">GLOBAL FUND LIST</uicontrol> page is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the list page, select the appropriate record to deactivate, and then perform either of the following:</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">In the toolbar, click  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Mark Active/Inactive</uicontrol>, and then click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Mark Inactive</uicontrol>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">In the toolbar, click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Edit</uicontrol>, clear  the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Is Active</uicontrol> check box, and then click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Save &amp; Exit</uicontrol>.</p>
                  </li>
               </ul>
            </info>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The selected record is marked as inactive.</info>
         </step>
      </steps>
